sourceMeaningMnemonic: Put a <radical>spirit</radical> in a <radical>black hole</radical> and a <kanji>duplicate</kanji> comes out. The duplicate looks exactly like the original spirit that went in. How strange.
meaningInfo: Examine the duplicate spirit. Same ghosty body. Same ghosty glow. A perfect copy.
readingMnemonic: Suddenly the <kanji>duplicate</kanji> spirit starts yelling, "Why did you throw me into that black hole?! <reading>F***</reading> (<ja>ふく</ja>) you!"
readingInfo: You feel pretty bad now. The duplicate spirit seems to have decided to haunt you, and it's muttering "F*** you, f*** you," over and over in your ear.
